-abstract method cannot be final
-abstract method cannot be static
-abstract method cannot be private
-Concrete static method is allowed inside an interface
-Static method of a class can be inherited but static method of an Interface cannot be inherited
-Static method, be it class or interface can never be overridden
-Static methods in an interface cannot be final whereas variables in an interface is final by default
-static method cannot be abstract
-We cannot create object of an Abstract class
-We can create constructor in an Abstract class
-If you create parametrized constructor in a child class, parent class will not be happy about it- because only non-parametrized constructor of child class can call non-parametrized constructor of parent class